reut2-001.sgm, U.S. LARD CONSUMPTION IN JANUARY, U.S. factory usage of lard in theproduction of both edible and inedible products during Januarytotaled 21.3 mln lbs, vs a revised 25.6 mln lbs in December,according to Census Bureau figures.    In the year-earlier period, usage, which includeshydrogenated vegetable and animal fats and other oils inprocess, amounted to 33.3 mln lbs.    Usage in January comprised 15.7 mln lbs of edible productsand 5.6 mln lbs of inedible products.    Total lard usage in the 1986/87 marketing season, whichbegan October 1, amounted to 104.3 mln lbs, vs 154.2 mln lbs inthe year-ago period. Reuter&#3;
