reut2-001.sgm, USDA TO REDUCE CITRUS ESTIMATING PROGRAM, the U.S. Agriculture Department'sNational Agricultural Statistics Services (NASS) said it willchange its citrus estimate program for California and Arizona,starting in 1988.    NASS said it will discontinue California forecasts forlemons during December, February, March, May and June and forgrapefruit and tangerines for those months plus November.    Forecasts for lemons will be issued in October, November,January, April and July and for grapefruit in October, January,April, and July and for tangerines in October,  January andApril. There will be no change in the estimating program forCalifornia oranges.    Arizona forecasts will be dropped for lemons, oranges,grapefruit and tangerines in November, December February,March, May and June, with forecasts retained in October,January, April and July, it said.    There will be no changes in the estimating program forcitrus in Texas or Florida. Reuter&#3;
