reut2-001.sgm, JAPAN CUTTING CHINA CORN COMMITMENTS - USDA, Japanese traders have apparentlysharply reduced commitments to buy Chinese corn over the nextsix months due to high prices, the U.S. Agriculture Departmentsaid.    In its World Production and Trade Report, the departmentsaid traders indicated China may lack supplies or be unwillingto sell at current low world prices.    If the reports are confirmed, China's major exportdestinations such as USSR, Japan, and South Korea, couldincrease purchases of U.S. corn, it said.    China is currently forecast to export 5.5 mln tonnes ofcorn during 1986/87 (Oct-Sept), it said. Reuter&#3;
