reut2-001.sgm, SURINAM GOVERNMENT TO DISCUSS ECONOMIC CRISIS, Surinam's military government opens afour-day congress tomorrow to discuss the country's deepeningeconomic crisis, the official Surinam News Agency reported.    Acting Prime Minister Jules Wijdenbosch will open themeeting which is being attended by government officials,political leaders and heads of labor unions.    Surinam's economy has suffered a sharp downturn in recentmonths as a result of guerrilla activities led by formersoldier Ronny Brunswijk, who is seeking to overthrow thegovernment of Commander Desi Bouterse.    The guerrillas have forced the shutdown of most ofSurinam's vital bauxite and aluminum industry, creating aforeign exchange crisis and food shortages. Reuter&#3;
